<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Hazardia</i> <i>squarrosa</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>aurantiacus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>cinereum</i>, <i>Eriophyllum</i> <i>confertiflorum</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i> and <i>Salvia</i> <i>leucophylla</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Juglans</i> <i>californica</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>lobata</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is open to intermittent and two tiered. Herbaceous layer is open to
intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Hazardia squarrosa</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Gentle to somewhat steep northeast facing slopes. Soils are fine clays.  </div>
</div>

        
