<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Hazardia squarrosa </i>vigorously sprouts after fire, and plants sprout and flower two years after a fire (Keeley and Keeley 1984). Seeds show highest germination rates without fire treatment in lighted conditions. These observations suggest that sprouting may be the predominant post-fire strategy as seed may not be stored in the soil between fires (Keeley 1987). Rather, seeds blown in from off-site sources and sprouts regenerate the alliance.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (20-100 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
